### DESIGN SYSTEM MIGRATION — DECISION TREE
# When migrating from dark_cyberpunk → light_tactical, the cognitive
# process follows this exact priority chain:

LAYER_0_foundation:
  index.css → CSS variables FIRST (all components inherit)
  tokens.ts → TypeScript constants (for inline styles)
  fonts     → Orbitron + Share Tech Mono loaded globally
  RATIONALE: Foundation layer means every component built AFTER this
             automatically gets correct fonts/colors. Components built
             BEFORE need surgical migration.

LAYER_1_shell:
  NewsTicker → 28px fixed top (z:150)
  HexodTopHUD → glassmorphism segments below ticker (z:100)
  HexodDock → hex-shaped bottom nav (z:100)
  RadarTrigger → left edge 48px (z:100)
  CRT scanlines → body::before (z:9999)
  RATIONALE: Shell components frame the entire UX. They must be built
             BEFORE removing legacy equivalents to avoid blank screens.
  CRITICAL: Build new + strip old in SAME SESSION. Never leave duplicates
            across sessions — user will see double UI.

LAYER_2_primitives:
  CrystalIcon → SVG diamond, replaces all emoji 💎 and 🪙
  GlassPanel → slide-in wrapper, replaces all dark motion.div panels
  Modal → glassmorphism overlay, replaces all fixed-position modals
  SubModal → stacks on modal with capture-phase Escape
  ModalTabBar → pill tabs consistent across all modules
  PillButton → consistent action buttons
  RATIONALE: Primitives BEFORE content migration. Each panel migration
             becomes a 3-line change: import GlassPanel, replace wrapper,
             adjust accent color.

LAYER_3_content_migration:
  PATTERN: For each existing panel:
    1. grep for 'motion.div.*fixed.*right.*#0' → find wrapper
    2. Add GlassPanel import
    3. Replace outer motion.div with <GlassPanel title= accent= width=>
    4. Remove old header (title + close button)
    5. Keep all content JSX unchanged
    6. Fix text colors: #fff → #1a2a3a, #6B7280 → rgba(26,42,58,0.45)
    7. Fix button colors: #00FF87 → #0099cc or accent, rgba(0,255,135) → rgba(0,153,204)
    8. Build test → commit
  SPEED: ~3 minutes per panel × 10 panels = 30 minutes total

